Patrick Odey, Uyo The Akwa Ibom State chapter of the People’s Democratic Party has announced Saturday as the commencement date for its congresses at the ward, local government and state levels. The exercise is for the election of party executives who will run the party’s affairs for the next four years. State chairman of the party, Paul Ekpo, said this at a media briefing in Uyo, on Thursday. Ekpo said, “In accordance with the approved amendments to our constitution, in the forthcoming nomination, the party intends to reserve six of the 17 positions in the executive for women at the ward level. The PDP chairman also said six out of the 18 positions in the executive would also be reserved for women at the local government level, and 13 out of the 39 positions in the exco for women at the state level. Three out of the 10 positions in the exco would be reserved for women at the zonal level, and nine out of the 28 positions in the Exco for women at the national level.” Copyright PUNCH.
